    detailedMechanism: `Dyspnea results from a mismatch between the brain's demand for ventilation and the body's ability to achieve it. Mechanoreceptors in the chest wall, chemoreceptors sensing CO2/O2, and receptors in the lungs all contribute to the sensation. Increased work of breathing (airway obstruction, stiff lungs), gas exchange problems (V/Q mismatch, diffusion impairment), or increased metabolic demand can all cause dyspnea.`,

