    localizationExplanation: `Location and character of symptoms help localize the problem. Dysuria
with suprapubic pain suggests cystitis. Dysuria with flank pain suggests pyelonephritis. Urethral
discharge suggests urethritis. Hesitancy and weak stream suggest obstruction (BPH). Urgency and
frequency without pain suggests overactive bladder. Stress incontinence (leakage with exertion)
suggests sphincter weakness. Urge incontinence suggests detrusor overactivity.`,
